    "explanation": "<p>Sertoli cells, located in the testes, play a critical role by providing nutritional support and an optimal environment for the development of sperm cells, a process known as spermatogenesis.</p>\n<p>Follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH) is vital in the reproductive system, particularly in females, as it stimulates the growth and maturation of ovarian follicles. Although the luteinizing hormone (LH) is responsible for triggering ovulation, FSH is crucial for preparing the follicles in the ovaries leading to ovulation.</p>\n<p>The placenta is responsible for producing human chorionic gonadotropin (hCG), a hormone necessary for sustaining pregnancy by supporting the ovarian production of progesterone.</p>\n<p>The urethra serves as the conduit connecting the bladder to the exterior of the body, allowing urine to be expelled.</p>",
